%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20America%20hasn't%20been%20able%20to%20put%20an%20end%20to%20sky-high%20prices%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20American%20flag%20overlapped%20with%20a%20price%20tag%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663d02fbb4abc992e8c77b01%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20persistence%20of%20inflation%20caught%20economists%2C%20analysts%2C%20and%2C%20most%20importantly%2C%20members%20of%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20by%20surprise.%3Cp%3ETyler%20Le%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20a%20difference%20three%20months%20makes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%202023%20and%20the%20start%20of%202024%2C%20it%20appeared%20that%20the%20US%20was%20on%20a%20glide%20path%20to%20what%20I%20termed%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2F2024-outlook-us-economy-stock-market-jobs-inflation-interest-rates-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeconomic%20nirvana%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%3A%20Growth%20would%20stay%20steady%2C%20if%20not%20spectacular%2C%20as%20inflation%20cooled%20off%20to%20a%20more%20manageable%20pace.%20This%20combination%20would%20not%20only%20let%20America%20continue%20its%20four-year%20expansion%20but%20also%20allow%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20to%20ease%20up%20on%20its%20attempts%20to%20rein%20in%20the%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20and%20maybe%20even%20cut%20interest%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20data%20released%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20months%20has%20forced%20me%20to%20reconsider%20my%20expectations%20for%20that%20nirvana%2C%20or%20at%20least%20the%20timing%20of%20its%20arrival.%20Recent%20signs%20point%20instead%20to%20an%20inflationary%20boom%3A%20a%20slightly%20hotter%20economy%20in%20which%20growth%20has%20stayed%20strong%20while%20inflation%20has%20sped%20back%20up.%20The%20labor%20market%20has%20been%20resilient%2C%20with%20recent%20jobs%20reports%20mostly%20coming%20in%20ahead%20of%20expectations%20and%20the%20Employment%20Cost%20Index%2C%20a%20widely%20followed%20measure%20of%20employee-compensation%20growth%2C%20picking%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20perhaps%20the%20most%20eye-catching%20development%20has%20been%20the%20persistence%20of%20inflation%2C%20which%20caught%20economists%2C%20analysts%2C%20and%2C%20most%20importantly%2C%20members%20of%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%20by%20surprise.%20The%20core%20personal%20consumption%20expenditures%20index%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Fed's%20favored%20inflation%20gauge%20that%20excludes%20volatile%20categories%20such%20as%20food%20and%20energy%20%E2%80%94%20has%20accelerated%2C%20undoing%20much%20of%20the%20progress%20from%20the%20previous%20six%20months.%20This%20inflationary-boom%20dynamic%20has%20pushed%20out%20expectations%20for%20rate%20cuts%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstagflation-recession-us-economy-outlook-gdp-dimon-inflation-rate-cuts-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecaused%20some%20more%20alarmist%20analysts%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20suggest%20that%20the%20US%20is%20about%20to%20be%20gripped%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstagflation-us-economy-gdp-growth-outlook-recession-forecast-inflation-rates-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanother%20bout%20of%20high%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20left%20some%20wondering%20whether%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhen-will-fed-cut-interest-rates-powell-fomc-inflation-relief-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFed's%20next%20move%20will%20instead%20be%20to%20hike%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%2C%20of%20course%2C%20fair%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftop-economist-us-economy-recession-federal-reserve-interest-rates-inflation-2022-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereevaluate%20one's%20expectations%20when%20new%20data%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20presented.%20Sticking%20with%20one's%20projection%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwall-street-scaremonger-economists-stock-market-analysts-cost-investors-money-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ejust%20to%20avoid%20being%20wrong%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20poor%20analysis.%20But%20after%20carefully%20examining%20the%20underlying%20inflation%20dynamics%20that%20have%20driven%20the%20recent%20freak-out%20about%20renewed%20overheating%2C%20I%20estimate%20the%20worries%20are%20overdone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20lead-up%20to%202024%2C%20the%20pace%20of%20price%20hikes%20was%20falling%20back%20to%20earth%20%E2%80%94%20or%20at%20least%20the%20Fed's%20goal%20of%202%25%20year%20over%20year.%20Core%20PCE%20rose%20at%20an%20annually%20adjusted%20rate%20of%201.9%25%20in%20the%20six%20months%20ending%20in%20December.%20It%20seemed%20like%20%26quot%3Bmission%20accomplished.%26quot%3B%20But%20in%20the%20first%20three%20months%20of%20this%20year%2C%20the%20measure%20heated%20back%20up%3A%20Core%20PCE%20surged%20to%204.4%25.%20Typically%2C%20price%20increases%20are%20a%20slow-moving%20process%2C%20so%20it%20is%20rare%20to%20see%20core%20inflation%20accelerate%20this%20much%20this%20quickly.%20When%20I%20started%20digging%20into%20the%20data%2C%20however%2C%20I%20had%20a%20hard%20time%20explaining%20the%20reversal%20based%20on%20the%20fundamentals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20think%20of%20inflation%20as%20a%20triangle%3A%20Each%20leg%20helps%20explain%20our%20overall%20price%20picture.%20The%20first%20leg%20is%20expectations%20%E2%80%94%20various%20surveys%20help%20gauge%20the%20degree%20to%20which%20inflation%20has%20become%20embedded%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20consumers%20and%20businesses.%20If%20these%20expectations%20start%20to%20creep%20up%2C%20that%20could%20be%20an%20indication%20that%20inflation%20is%20soon%20to%20follow.%20The%20second%20element%20is%20aggregate%20demand%3A%20If%20people%20suddenly%20have%20more%20to%20spend%2C%20that%20can%20push%20up%20spending%20and%20cause%20prices%20to%20rise%20along%20with%20it.%20One%20way%20to%20measure%20this%20is%20unemployment%20%E2%80%94%20if%20there%20is%20a%20sudden%20surge%20in%20Americans%20getting%20new%20jobs%2C%20demand%20is%20likely%20to%20jump%20as%20well.%20The%20final%20piece%20is%20supply%20shocks%3A%20How%20much%20have%20one-off%20disruptions%20helped%20raise%20prices%20on%20things%20like%20imported%20consumer%20goods%20or%20oil%3F%20Using%20this%20framework%2C%20it's%20difficult%20to%20pinpoint%20why%20inflation%20has%20strengthened%20so%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Survey%20of%20Professional%20Forecasters%20has%20found%20longer-run%20expectations%20for%20inflation%20have%20leveled%20out%20at%202%25%20%E2%80%94%20the%20Fed's%20target.%20The%20unemployment%20rate%20is%20up%20modestly%20from%2012%20months%20ago%2C%20which%20suggests%20that%20price%20hikes%20aren't%20being%20driven%20by%20a%20sudden%20surge%20in%20consumer%20or%20household%20demand.%20And%20there%20have%20been%20no%20widespread%20supply%20bottlenecks%20to%20speak%20of.%20The%20ISM%20vendor-deliveries%20index%2C%20which%20measures%20the%20amount%20of%20time%20purchasing%20managers%20have%20to%20wait%20to%20get%20the%20goods%20they%20need%2C%20indicates%20that%20the%20supply%20chain%20is%20running%20smoothly.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2Fww2J9%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Expert%20predictions%20for%20future%20inflation%20are%20cooling%20off%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22459%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20deeper%20level%2C%20it%20appears%20that%20the%20acceleration%20in%20inflation%20is%20somewhat%20random%2C%20with%20much%20of%20the%20recent%20pickup%20being%20driven%20by%20industry-specific%20factors%20as%20opposed%20to%20overall%20economic%20conditions.%20Healthcare-services%20inflation%20is%20a%20notable%20example.%20PCE%20inflation%20includes%20both%20what%20consumers%20pay%20out%20of%20pocket%20for%20their%20care%20and%20payments%20made%20on%20behalf%20of%20individuals%20by%20employers%20or%20the%20government.%20Well%2C%20because%20of%20government%20rule%20adjustments%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%2C%20Medicaid%20payments%20surged%2C%20helping%20to%20drive%20up%20the%20overall%20index.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20cost%20of%20financial%20services%20went%20up%20as%20fees%20paid%20to%20financial%20advisors%20increased%2C%20but%20this%20is%20simply%20a%20lagged%20response%20to%20the%20strong%20performance%20of%20the%20stock%20market%20at%20the%20end%20of%202023.%20Since%20fees%20are%20a%20set%20percentage%20of%20a%20person's%20portfolio%2C%20the%20big%20run-up%20in%20equities%20at%20the%20end%20of%20last%20year%20meant%20that%20people%20may%20have%20paid%20more%20in%20total%20dollars%20to%20their%20advisor%2C%20but%20that's%20only%20because%20the%20value%20of%20their%20investments%20was%20also%20soaring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20one-offs%20have%20had%20an%20outsize%20impact%20on%20the%20overall%20inflation%20picture.%20Ahead%20of%202024%2C%20the%20contribution%20from%20acyclical%20components%20to%20core%20inflation%20was%20essentially%20zero.%20Over%20the%20past%20three%20months%2C%20it%20has%20swelled%20to%204.4%25.%20By%20contrast%2C%20the%20impact%20of%20cyclical%20components%20%E2%80%94%20those%20elements%20that%20are%20correlated%20to%20the%20overall%20health%20of%20the%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20on%20inflation%20has%20slowed%20marginally%20since%20last%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20nature%20of%20the%20recent%20hot%20inflation%20readings%2C%20the%20fundamental%20case%20for%20a%20return%20to%20the%20path%20of%20nirvana%20is%20strong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%20thing%2C%20economic%20growth%20is%20not%20getting%20away%20from%20the%20Fed.%20If%20growth%20were%20materially%20accelerating%2C%20it%20would%20drive%20up%20the%20demand%20leg%20of%20the%20inflation%20stool%2C%20increasing%20prices%20as%20Americans%20went%20out%20and%20threw%20around%20their%20newfound%20cash.%20But%20that's%20not%20what's%20happening.%20Real%20GDP%20rose%20at%20a%201.6%25%20annualized%20pace%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%2C%20with%20private%20demand%20%E2%80%94%20which%20excludes%20company%20inventory%20buildups%2C%20government%20spending%2C%20and%20net%20exports%20%E2%80%94%20climbing%203.1%25.%20The%20strong%20growth%20in%20private%20demand%20suggests%20that%20second-quarter%20GDP%20could%20be%20even%20more%20robust.%20Rather%20than%20a%20sudden%20reignition%20of%20the%20economy%2C%20the%20under-the-hood%20data%20suggests%20that%20this%20is%20simply%20the%20US%20settling%20into%20a%20steady-state%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20one%2C%20investments%20in%20residential%20real%20estate%20surged%2C%20adding%20half%20a%20percentage%20point%20to%20GDP%20in%20the%20first%20quarter.%20But%20with%20borrowing%20rates%20rising%20and%20building%20permits%20declining%2C%20that%20kind%20of%20housing%20contribution%20is%20unlikely%20to%20repeat.%20Second%2C%20the%20rise%20in%20consumption%20over%20the%20past%20two%20months%20was%20driven%20almost%20entirely%20by%20declines%20in%20the%20savings%20rate.%20Put%20another%20way%2C%20Americans%20were%20fueling%20their%20purchases%20by%20dipping%20into%20their%20cash%20reserves.%20I%20would%20not%20expect%20households%20to%20dip%20into%20their%20savings%20quite%20as%20much%20going%20forward%2C%20especially%20since%20wage%20growth%20is%20still%20moderating.%20The%20Indeed%20Wage%20Tracker%2C%20a%20measure%20of%20changes%20in%20wages%20and%20salaries%20advertised%20in%20job%20postings%20on%20Indeed%2C%20has%20been%20steadily%20slowing%20%E2%80%94%20down%20to%203.1%25%20growth%20over%20the%20past%20year.%20This%20measure%20tends%20to%20move%20ahead%20of%20the%20more%20widely%20followed%20Wage%20Growth%20Tracker%20from%20the%20Atlanta%20Fed%20by%20roughly%20eight%20months.%20Add%20all%20this%20up%2C%20and%20it%20paints%20a%20picture%20of%20a%20resilient%20but%20certainly%20not%20red-hot%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22breakout-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FWHlOV%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Wage%20growth%20appears%20to%20be%20moderating%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22465%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20surprised%20at%20how%20quickly%20equity%20markets%20have%20shrugged%20off%20the%20inflation%20news.%20If%20inflation%20persists%20as%20it%20has%2C%20it%20introduces%20real%20downside%20risks%20to%20growth.%20Real%20incomes%20will%20slow%20as%20inflation%20remains%20strong%2C%20which%20will%20weigh%20on%20household%20consumption%20and%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20corporate%20earnings.%20This%20is%20not%20like%20last%20year.%20The%20labor%20markets%20are%20not%20in%20the%20same%20place.%20Thus%2C%20instead%20of%20reinforcing%20the%20inflationary-boom%20narrative%2C%20stronger%20inflation%20today%20implies%20more%20of%20a%20downside%20risk%20to%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20good%20news%20is%20that%20there%20are%20strong%20reasons%20to%20expect%20the%20recent%20pickup%20in%20US%20inflation%20to%20fade.%20Expectations%20are%20steady%2C%20labor-market%20turnover%20remains%20low%2C%20and%20inflation%20continues%20to%20moderate%20in%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20developed%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20terms%20of%20an%20outlook%20for%20the%20market%2C%20the%20upshot%20is%20that%20if%20my%20analysis%20is%20right%2C%20the%20slowing%20in%20core%20inflation%20and%20stability%20in%20economic%20growth%20ought%20to%20renew%20some%20of%20the%20enthusiasm%20for%20the%20prospects%20of%20a%20soft%20landing.%20If%20that's%20right%2C%20I'd%20take%20bonds%20over%20stocks%20for%20the%20time%20being%2C%20though%20they%20should%20both%20do%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBringing%20inflation%20down%20from%20multidecade%20highs%20was%20never%20going%20to%20be%20a%20simple%20or%20straightforward%20task%20%E2%80%94%20the%20start%20of%20the%20year%20has%20proved%20as%20much.%20Expecting%20inflation%20to%20continue%20its%20downward%20trend%20is%20not%20a%20matter%20of%20keeping%20the%20faith.%20It's%20a%20clear%20reading%20of%20what%20the%20data%20is%20really%20telling%20us%3A%20Nirvana%20is%20still%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fneil-dutta%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3ENeil%20Dutta%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0is%20head%20of%20economics%20at%20Renaissance%20Macro%20Research.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-prices-inflation-sticking-interest-rate-hikes-stock-market-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715592421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663d03439686a6f37bfdd5b2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-prices-inflation-sticking-interest-rate-hikes-stock-market-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20sudden%20resurgence%20of%20inflation%20has%20caused%20some%20more%20alarmist%20analysts%20to%20suggest%20that%20the%20US%20economy%20is%20in%20deep%20trouble.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Neil%20Dutta)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhigh-prices-inflation-sticking-interest-rate-hikes-stock-market-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Arizona%20is%20a%20cautionary%20tale%20for%20school%20vouchers%20as%20a%20wave%20of%20states%20are%20giving%20parents%20cash%20to%20send%20their%20kids%20to%20private%20school%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kid%20in%20a%20classroom%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663bd7789686a6f37bfd66ef%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBlend%20Images%20-%20Tanya%20Constantine%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EArizona%20established%20a%20universal%20school%20voucher%20system%20to%20allow%20kids%20to%20switch%20from%20public%20to%20private%20school.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAn%20expert%20told%20BI%20that%20vouchers%20tend%20to%20go%20to%20wealthy%20families.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt's%C2%A0%26quot%3Ba%20cautionary%20tale%26quot%3B%20for%20all%20the%20other%20states%20expanding%20voucher%20systems%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20prominence%20of%20school%20vouchers%20continues%20to%20surge%20across%20the%20country%20%E2%80%94%20but%20they%20might%20not%20benefit%20the%20families%20who%20need%20them%20the%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20states%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news5cleveland.com%2Fnews%2Flocal-news%2Finvestigations%2Fevery-ohio-family-can-now-get-a-private-school-voucher-some-say-it-helps-students-experts-call-it-harmful%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOhio%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farkansasadvocate.com%2F2024%2F04%2F02%2Farkansas-governor-marks-start-of-year-two-for-voucher-applications%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EArkansas%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20expanded%20their%20school%20voucher%20programs%20to%20allow%20most%20or%20all%20parents%20to%20receive%20funding%20to%20send%20their%20kids%20to%20private%20schools.%20More%20than%2020%20states%20now%20have%20some%20kind%20of%20voucher%20program%20with%20more%20in%20consideration.%20Arizona%20was%20the%20first%20state%20to%20create%20a%20universal%20voucher%20program%20in%202022%20%E2%80%94%20and%20experts%20have%20said%20it's%20the%20state%20to%20watch%20when%20analyzing%20the%20impact%20of%20vouchers%20for%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20modern%20school%20voucher%20movement%20started%20to%20grow%20in%20the%201990s%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eunder%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20government%20would%20give%20parents%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20money%20to%20put%20toward%20private%20school%20tuition.%20The%20programs%20were%20means-tested%2C%20meaning%20recipients%20had%20to%20meet%20a%20certain%20poverty%20limit%20to%20receive%20assistance%2C%20with%20the%20idea%20that%20kids%20with%20fewer%20resources%20would%20be%20able%20to%20earn%20a%20better%20education%20at%20private%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20gradually%2C%20more%20states%20began%20to%20raise%20the%20poverty%20limit%2C%20making%20nearly%20any%20parent%20eligible%20to%20receive%20the%20funding%20%E2%80%94%20and%20in%20some%20states%2C%20it%20led%20to%20the%20cash%20going%20to%20the%20wealthiest%20families.%20Arizona%20is%20%26quot%3Ba%20cautionary%20tale%26quot%3B%20regarding%20the%20expansion%20of%20vouchers%2C%20Josh%20Cowen%2C%20professor%20of%20education%20policy%20at%20Michigan%20State%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20Arizona%20expansion%2C%20it's%20just%20going%20into%20communities%20that%20are%20primarily%20wealthy%2C%26quot%3B%20Cowen%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20this%20thing%20stopped%20becoming%20a%20means%20test%2020%20years%20ago%2C%20it%20stopped%20being%20an%20antipoverty%20device.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Farizonas-universal-education-savings-account-program-has-become-a-handout-to-the-wealthy%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Brookings%20Institution%20delved%20further%20into%20the%20implications%20of%20Arizona's%20voucher%20program.%20Arizona%20was%20the%20first%20state%20to%20implement%20a%20universal%20education%20savings%20account%20%E2%80%94%20which%20the%20state%20calls%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.azed.gov%2Fesa%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEmpowerment%20Scholarship%20Account%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20to%20allow%20parents%20to%20receive%20state%20funding%20to%20send%20their%20kids%20to%20private%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20program%20initially%20was%20capped%20to%20students%20with%20disabilities%2C%20it%20gradually%20expanded%20to%20include%20more%20students%2C%20and%20it's%20now%20open%20to%20all%20students%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20wealthiest%20are%20disproportionately%20getting%20the%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EArizona%20is%20just%20one%20example%20of%20the%20range%20of%20programs%20across%20over%2020%20states%20implementing%20voucher%20programs.%20While%20they've%20been%20championed%20by%20many%20Republican%20legislators%20who%20have%20argued%20that%20the%20vouchers%20allow%20parents%20to%20control%20what%20their%20kids%20are%20learning%2C%20critics%20have%20argued%20that%20they've%20diverted%20funds%20from%20public%20schools%20and%20lack%20accountability%20measures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20an%20analysis%20of%20the%202024%20second-quarter%20report%20for%20the%20program%2C%20Brookings%20found%20that%20the%20lowest-poverty%20areas%20in%20Arizona%20tend%20to%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehave%20the%20highest%20participation%20in%20the%20ESA%20program%2C%20and%20the%20area%20with%20the%20lowest%20median%20income%20also%20has%20the%20lowest%20ESA%20participation%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20the%20zip%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecodes%20with%20the%20lowest%20poverty%20rate%2C%20like%20Phoenix%20suburb%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EQueen%20Creek%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ehad%20the%20highest%20participation%20rate%20of%2075%20recipients%20per%201%2C000%20children%20under%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20noted%20that%20there%20are%20a%20range%20of%20reasons%20families%20in%20higher%20poverty%20areas%20might%20not%20be%20participating%20in%20the%20program%2C%20including%20being%20unaware%20of%20the%20program%20or%20unable%20to%20get%20to%20their%20preferred%20school%20due%20to%20transportation%20barriers.%20Cost%20is%20also%20a%20barrier%2C%20the%20report%20said%2C%20since%20tuition%20at%20private%20schools%20often%20exceeds%20the%20scholarship%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRegardless%2C%20if%20states%20that%20have%20adopted%20(or%20are%20considering)%20universal%20ESA%20programs%20are%20serious%20about%20using%20private%20school%20choice%20to%20address%20inequities%20in%20school%20access%2C%20they%20need%20to%20take%20a%20hard%20look%20at%20these%20programs%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20data%20emerging%20from%20Arizona%20provide%20plenty%20of%20reasons%20for%20concern.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Arizona%20Gov.%20Katie%20Hobbs%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663bd7ac9686a6f37bfd6709%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22512%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EArizona%20Gov.%20Katie%20Hobbs%20introduced%20an%20effort%20to%20boost%20transparency%20in%20the%20voucher%20system.%3Cp%3ERebecca%20Noble%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%227592e468-549f-4814-a8b2-978e30665e85%5C%22%3EThe%20complicated%20future%20of%20school%20vouchers%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EArizona's%20former%20GOP%20Governor%20Doug%20Ducey%20made%20the%20state's%20ESAs%20universal%20in%202022%2C%20later%20saying%20during%20a%20February%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Freason.com%2F2024%2F02%2F24%2Fformer-arizona-gov-doug-ducey-on-spending-and-school-choice%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterview%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20during%20remote%20learning%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%26quot%3Bparents%20were%20able%20to%20see%20what%20their%20kids%20were%20being%20taught%20or%20not%20taught%20and%20the%20level%20of%20rigor%20and%20expectation%20from%20the%20public%20schools.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey%20also%20saw%20that%20the%20charter%20schools%20opened%20and%20the%20Catholic%20schools%20opened%20and%20many%20of%20the%20largest%20public%20districts%20chose%20to%20stay%20closed%20for%20nearly%20two%20years%2C%20even%20when%20the%20government%20was%20telling%20them%20to%20open%2C%26quot%3B%20Ducey%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERepublican%20members%20of%20the%20legislature%20have%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fazcapitoltimes.com%2Fnews%2F2024%2F01%2F08%2Ffreedom-caucus-slams-hobbs-plan-to-regulate-school-vouchers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esupported%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20expansion%20of%20vouchers%2C%20emphasizing%20that%20parents%20should%20have%20a%20role%20in%20choosing%20their%20kids'%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Katie%20Hobbs%2C%20the%20state's%20current%20Democratic%20governor%2C%20proposed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fazgovernor.gov%2Foffice-arizona-governor%2Fnews%2F2024%2F01%2Fgovernor-katie-hobbs-announces-plan-esa-accountability-and%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eplan%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20January%20to%20rein%20in%20the%20program%20as%20part%20of%20an%20effort%20to%20address%20budget%20deficits.%20Her%20plan%20would%20require%20students%20to%20attend%20a%20public%20school%20for%20100%20days%20at%20any%20point%20in%20their%20education%20before%20becoming%20eligible%20for%20a%20voucher.%20It%20would%20also%20establish%20transparency%20measures%20that%20would%20ensure%2C%20for%20example%2C%20vouchers%20do%20not%20pay%20for%20extravagant%20field%20trips.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20plan%20is%20simple%3A%20every%20school%20receiving%20taxpayer%20dollars%20must%20have%20basic%20standards%20to%20show%20they're%20keeping%20our%20students%20safe%20and%20giving%20Arizona%20children%20the%20education%20they%20deserve%2C%26quot%3B%20Hobbs%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20Arizona%20got%20a%20head%20start%20on%20implementing%20its%20voucher%20program%2C%20other%20states%20are%20following%20suit.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nea.org%2Fnea-today%2Fall-news-articles%2Fno-accountability-vouchers-wreak-havoc-states%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAt%20least%20eleven%3C%2Fa%3E%20now%20have%20universal%20programs%2C%20and%20other%20states%2C%20including%20Tennessee%2C%20Georgia%2C%20and%20Alabama%2C%20are%20considering%20new%20laws.%20Arizona%20could%20preview%20not%20only%20budget%20complications%20for%20other%20states%20but%20a%20rocky%20outlook%20for%20the%20future%20of%20public%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20see%20these%20vouchers%20start%20to%20cannibalize%20on%20public%20school%20funds.%20The%20most%20important%20piece%20probably%20is%20at%20that%20state%20level%20where%20you%20really%20are%20talking%20about%20taking%20up%20a%20huge%20portion%20of%20dollars%20that%20the%20state%20can%20be%20spending%20on%20other%20things%2C%20like%20public%20schools%2C%20but%20also%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Cowen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20amount%20of%20money%20that%20you're%20spending%20on%20this%20means%20that%20at%20some%20point%2C%20there%20are%20real%20meaningful%20policy%20trade-offs%2C%20and%20not%20all%20dollars%20are%20created%20equal%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BSo%20for%20schools%2C%20the%20state%20aid%20portion%20is%20really%2C%20really%20important.%20It's%20the%20important%20equalizer%20at%20the%20local%20level%20between%20districts%20that%20might%20have%20very%20different%20tax%20bases%20to%20draw%20from.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20you%20received%20a%20school%20voucher%20or%20decided%20not%20to%20participate%20in%20your%20state's%20program%3F%20Are%20you%20in%20a%20state%20considering%20school%20vouchers%3F%20Share%20your%20story%20with%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aasheffey%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Easheffey%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%2