%20in%20New%20York%20City%20when%20I%20arrived%2C%20so%20he%20asked%20if%20I%20would%20like%20to%20work%20at%20the%20same%20fast-food%20company%20he%20worked%20at.%20I%20started%20earning%20%24500%20a%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20two%20months%20of%20navigating%20the%20city's%20streets%20on%20a%20bicycle%2C%20I%20realized%20I%20didn't%20enjoy%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEveryone%20was%20always%20in%20a%20hurry%2C%20and%20I%20saw%20several%20delivery%20riders%20get%20into%20accidents.%20I%20decided%20to%20look%20for%20another%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22415cfa81-8dec-4718-8083-426209e91f02%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChef's%20assistant%2C%20%24620%20a%20week%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20told%20a%20friend%20in%20the%20industry%20that%20I%20was%20ready%20to%20leave%20and%20wanted%20to%20get%20into%20cooking.%20I'm%20not%20trained%20as%20a%20professional%20chef%2C%20but%20I've%20always%20enjoyed%20cooking.%20As%20a%20young%20boy%2C%20I'd%20join%20my%20grandmother%20in%20the%20kitchen%20and%20help%20her%20make%20mixiote%2C%20a%20Mexican%20dish%20of%20meat%20and%20spices%20wrapped%20in%20a%20maguey%20leaf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20friend%20told%20me%20Essex%20World%20Caf%C3%A9%20was%20seeking%20a%20chef's%20assistant.%20I%20applied%20and%20got%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20learned%20a%20lot%20about%20camaraderie%20and%20teamwork.%20I%20also%20learned%20how%20to%20work%20with%20ingredients%2C%20make%20sauces%2C%20and%20prepare%20each%20type%20of%20meat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20eight%20hours%20a%20day%20and%20earned%20%24620%20a%20week.%20After%20three%20years%2C%20I%20felt%20I'd%20gone%20as%20far%20as%20I%20could%20in%20that%20position%2C%20so%20I%20looked%20for%20a%20job%20in%20a%20larger%20restaurant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2228ac15cb-6bfb-4430-856f-d318dfedd7b1%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELine%20cook%2C%20%24710%20a%20week%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20next%20role%20put%20me%20in%20the%20hot%20seat.%20Another%20friend%20also%20told%20me%20about%20this%20job.%20I%20became%20a%20line%20cook%20at%20Pacific%20Grill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Flearning%2Fline-cook-coding-boot-camp-online-courses-software-engineer-career-change-pandemic%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELine%20cooks%3C%2Fa%3E%20work%20as%20a%20team.%20One%20manages%20the%20grill%2C%20another%20manages%20the%20fry%2C%20and%2C%20in%20the%20middle%2C%20someone%20handles%20the%20pans.%20I%20was%20in%20the%20middle%20in%20charge%20of%20pasta%20and%20saut%C3%A9ed%20vegetables.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20never%20got%20bored.%20I%20loved%20the%20pressure%20of%20producing%20the%20perfect%20dish%20at%20a%20certain%20speed%2C%20but%20that%20pressure%20sometimes%20stressed%20me%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stayed%20for%20two%20years%20but%20left%20when%20they%20closed%20the%20restaurant%20to%20remodel%20it%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b69a2352-ac59-4608-ac17-038fd90aff15%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ELine%20cook%2C%20%24820%20a%20week%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20next%20joined%20a%20restaurant%20called%20Extra%20Virgin%20in%20the%20West%20Village%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20line%20cook%20again%2C%20producing%20desserts%20and%20salads%20for%20%24820%20a%20week.%20I%20learned%20how%20to%20make%20Mediterranean%20foods%20and%20dabbled%20in%20making%20my%20own%20dressings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20owner%20was%20also%20the%20chef%2C%20so%20everything%20had%20to%20be%20perfect%2C%20well-arranged%2C%20and%20flavorful.%20I%20had%20a%20fantastic%20experience%20working%20in%20that%20restaurant%20and%20stayed%20for%20three%20years.%20The%20most%20challenging%20aspect%20was%20having%20the%20boss%20work%20alongside%20me%20in%20the%20kitchen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d27987ec-7878-456e-99cc-d46d39c4a31a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EDishwasher%2C%20%24790%20for%20four%20days%20a%20week%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20network%20grew%2C%20and%20another%20friend%20told%20me%20about%20a%20startup%20called%20Cook%20Unity%20in%202016.%20I%20didn't%20know%20anything%20about%20it%20and%20wasn't%20sure%20if%20it%20was%20for%20me%2C%20but%20my%20friend%20gave%20me%20the%20owner's%20number%20and%20asked%20me%20to%20call%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECook%20Unity%20is%20a%20chef-to-customer%20meal%20subscription%20platform%20based%20in%20Brooklyn.%20Customers%20order%20ready-to-eat%20meals%20from%20an%20online%20menu%20and%20see%20which%20chef%20wrote%20the%20recipe.%20The%20chefs%2C%20who%20are%20private%20contractors%2C%20earn%20up%20to%20a%20%243%20commission%20for%20every%20dish%20they%20sell%20that's%20prepared%20using%20their%20recipe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20met%20the%20owner%2C%20he%20explained%20they%20were%20looking%20for%20chefs%20but%20didn't%20have%20any%20line%20cook%20positions%20available.%20I%20had%20gained%20a%20lot%20of%20experience%20and%20knew%20a%20lot%20of%20recipes%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20say%20I%20was%20a%20chef.%20The%20only%20other%20job%20they%20had%20available%20was%20a%20dishwasher.%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20company%2C%20so%20I%20became%20a%20dishwasher.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20a%20dishwasher%20is%20a%20very%20tough%20job%2C%20as%20the%20chefs%20want%20the%20kitchen%20to%20be%20immaculate%20at%20all%20times.%20Over%20the%20next%20year%2C%20I%20saw%20the%20dynamics%20of%20how%20the%20chefs%20and%20the%20team%20worked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20earned%20%24790%20for%20four%20days%20a%20week%20of%20work%2C%20so%20I%20had%20extra%20time%20for%20my%20music%20hobby.%20I%20played%20in%20a%20mariachi%20band%20and%20still%20play%20when%20I%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e0f89e80-0768-442e-9caf-1b1998eabfba%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EKitchen%20manager%2C%20%2445%2C000%20a%20year%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20I%20was%20asked%20if%20I%20would%20like%20to%20become%20a%20kitchen%20manager.%20My%20role%20was%20to%20work%20with%20the%20chefs%20and%20ensure%20they%20had%20all%20the%20ingredients%20they%20needed%20for%20the%20dishes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20of%20the%20Cook%20Unity%20chefs%20has%20a%20different%20menu%2C%20so%20I%20had%20to%20learn%20about%20various%20ingredients%20from%20different%20parts%20of%20the%20world.%20I%20worked%20between%2012%20and%2014%20hours%20a%20day%20and%20earned%20a%20salary%20of%20%2445%2C000%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20a%20kitchen%20manager%20until%20the%20pandemic%20hit%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221d777f39-d985-4ce0-91a0-972bd4b61fa8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChef%2C%20%24969%2C000%20a%20year%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202020%2C%20I%20became%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cookunity.com%2Fchefs%2Fandres-mendez%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echef%20for%20Cook%20Unity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20transitioning%20from%20full-time%20employment%20to%20being%20a%20contractor.%20I%20started%20creating%20recipes%2C%20and%20the%20sous%20chefs%20and%20cooks%20made%20my%20dishes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20my%20dishes%20were%20only%20sold%20in%20New%20York%2C%20but%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20need%20for%20food%20delivery%20services%20rose.%20My%20earnings%20started%20to%20increase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20receive%20a%20commission%20from%20the%20sale%20of%20each%20of%20my%20dishes.%20In%202021%2C%20I%20earned%20%24969%2C000.%20Cook%20Unity%20expanded%20to%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20Miami%2C%20Chicago%2C%20Austin%2C%20Atlanta%2C%20and%20Seattle.%20Now%2C%2085%20sous%20chefs%20and%20cooks%20across%20the%20country%20produce%20my%20dishes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2242f9f8d5-16a4-4b0e-bb11-8bb01b6ae33e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EChef%2C%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cstrong%3E%243%2C000%2C000%20a%20year%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%202023%2C%20I%20was%20earning%20over%20%243%20million.%20I%20sell%2010%2C000%20to%2011%2C000%20meals%20weekly%20in%20New%20York%20and%20Los%20Angeles.%20My%20goal%20is%20to%20sell%20that%20many%20in%20each%20of%20the%20other%20cities%20and%20continue%20to%20provide%20job%20opportunities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20my%20rise%20in%20earnings%20felt%20like%20a%20dream.%20It%20was%20a%20big%20accomplishment%20for%20me.%20My%20friends%20are%20extremely%20happy%20for%20me%2C%20and%20I%20offer%20advice%20to%20my%20friends%20who%20are%20chefs%20when%20they%20need%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20week%2C%20I%20create%20recipes%20and%20cook%2C%20but%20on%20the%20weekends%2C%20I%20spend%20time%20with%20my%20wife%20and%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20bought%20a%20farm%20in%20Mexico%20where%20I%20employ%2020%20people.%20I%20plan%20to%20buy%20another%20home%20in%20Mexico%20or%20Texas.%20I'm%20extremely%20proud%20of%20how%20I%20can%20give%20my%20family%20a%20better%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchef-3-million-year-career-progression-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715591102000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F663e34ecb4abc992e8c7fd62%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchef-3-million-year-career-progression-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Andres%20Mendez%20moved%20to%20NYC%20when%20he%20was%2016%20and%20started%20work%20as%20a%20food%20delivery%20driver.%2015%20years%20later%2C%20he%20earns%20seven%20figures%20as%20a%20professional%20chef.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Claire%20Turrell)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchef-3-million-year-career-progression-2024-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22LS%20polls%202024%3A%201.4%20bn%20people%20will%20make%20'400%20paar'%20a%20reality%2C%20says%20PM%20Modi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1715591014000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-04%2F26%2Fthumb%2Ffitandfill%2F400X400%2F1714130800-8998.jpg%22%2C%22origi