20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20blue%20mannequin%20is%20wearing%20a%20pair%20of%20Google's%20smart%20glasses%2C%20known%20as%20Google%20Glass.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66101a9d3f923f7dab0505b8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoogle%20Glass%2C%20Google's%20smart%20glasses%2C%20were%20meant%20to%20be%20revolutionary%20but%20were%20released%20before%20they%20were%20ready%20and%20had%20a%20number%20of%20quality%20issues.%3Cp%3EMandel%20Ngan%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle%20Glass%20existed%20for%20almost%20exactly%2010%20years%20before%20being%20discontinued.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle%20Glass'%20failure%20came%20amid%20widespread%20quality%20issues%20and%20a%20general%20lack%20of%20adoption.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EApple's%20smart%20glasses%2C%20the%20Apple%20Vision%20Pro%2C%20seem%20to%20be%20succeeding%20where%20Google%20Glass%20failed.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%20announced%20in%202012%2C%20and%20then%20released%20to%20a%20select%20number%20of%20product%20testers%20in%202013%2C%20Google%20Glass%20was%20thought%20by%20many%20tech%20experts%20and%20industry%20watchers%20to%20be%20a%20revolutionary%20new%20device%20that%20would%20change%20the%20way%20human%20beings%20and%20technology%20interacted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20benefit%20of%20hindsight%2C%20we%20now%20know%20those%20hopes%20were%20overblown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20what%20went%20wrong%3F%20A%20cocktail%20of%20factors%20led%20to%20the%20failure%20of%20Google%20Glass.%20But%20before%20we%20discuss%20the%20demise%2C%20let's%20establish%20a%20baseline%20understanding%20of%20this%20once-promising%20hardware.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221e67484e-f6a2-4aaf-a9ed-1b85bbf4e661%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20did%20Google%20Glass%20do%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20Glass%20was%20first%20developed%20by%20a%20lab%20formerly%20known%20as%20Google%20X.%20The%20secretive%20research%20initiative%2C%20which%20also%20developed%20the%20self-driving%20car%20technology%20now%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwaymo-self-driving-robotaxi-cars-without-drivers-amazing-tech-review-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWaymo%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20now%20a%20subsidiary%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-alphabet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlphabet%2C%20Google's%20parent%20company%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20Glass%20was%20like%20a%20heads-up%20display%20and%20a%20mini%20computer%20joined%20together%20in%20one%20pair%20of%20glasses.%20It%20placed%20a%20small%20cube%20of%20glass%20just%20before%20its%20wearer's%20right%20eye%20and%20had%20a%20camera%20inset%20into%20the%20frame%20beside%20that%20cube.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20camera%20could%20be%20used%20to%20do%20things%20like%20identify%20objects%20or%20locations%20or%20project%20a%20restaurant's%20menu%20or%20a%20subway%20station's%20schedule%20before%20the%20user's%20vision%20in%20real%20time.%20It%20could%20also%20share%20images%20and%20videos%20via%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-google-meet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Meet%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20Glass%20even%20integrated%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fgoogle-calendar-tips%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Calendar%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20could%20show%20wearers%20their%20schedules%20or%20event%20notifications.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20Glass%20used%20the%20Google%20search%20engine%20to%20summon%20information%2C%20allowing%20wearers%20to%20navigate%20the%20world%20hands-free%20and%20with%20their%20eyes%20raised%20from%20their%20phone%20while%20still%20enjoying%20all%20the%20benefits%20of%20a%20smart%20device.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hardware%20was%20controlled%20via%20voice%20command%20or%20a%20touchpad%20on%20the%20side%20of%20the%20frame.%20Google%20Glass%20could%20also%20do%20many%20things%20a%20smartphone%20can%2C%20like%20send%20and%20receive%20texts%2C%20take%20photos%2C%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22115dbb89-c055-4f7e-9416-c6a413f94eb5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20did%20Google%20Glass%20fail%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Google%20co-founder%20Sergey%20Brin%20stands%20on%20a%20stage%20with%20colleagues%20to%20present%20a%20version%20of%20the%20Google%20Glass%20smart%20glasses.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6613fc451caec1275a6da822%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221345%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGoogle%20launched%20several%20editions%20of%20Google%20Glass%20%E2%80%94%20some%20for%20consumers%20and%20others%20for%20businesses%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0but%20none%20achieved%20widespread%20adoption.%20%3Cp%3EKimihiro%20Hoshino%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20Glass%20was%20released%20before%20it%20was%20ready.%20Early%20users%20complained%20about%20short%20battery%20life%2C%20slow%20upload%20times%2C%20inferior%20camera%20quality%2C%20and%20spotty%20voice%20control%20and%20voice%20recognition%20abilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20system%20often%20misheard%20words%20and%20was%20unable%20to%20pick%20up%20commands%20over%20loud%20background%20noise.%20And%20despite%20being%20essentially%20a%20smart%20pair%20of%20glasses%2C%20the%20physical%20design%20of%20early%20Google%20Glass%20editions%20was%20not%20that%20smart%3A%20the%20arms%20of%20the%20glasses%20did%20not%20fold%20down%2C%20so%20storing%20a%20Google%20Glass%20when%20it%20was%20not%20being%20worn%20was%20a%20frustration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20must%20be%20said%20that%2C%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20Google%20Glass%20was%20an%20answer%20to%20a%20problem%20that%20did%20not%20exist.%20Despite%20the%20best%20efforts%20of%20Google%20co-founder%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-sergey-brin-called-convinced-employee-to-stay-reject-openai-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESergey%20Brin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20frequently%20wore%20the%20glasses%20in%20public%2C%20the%20public%20did%20not%20have%20much%20interest%20in%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20many%20people%20hated%20the%20sense%20that%20they%20were%20always%20being%20filmed%20and%20monitored%20by%20people%20wearing%20Google%20Glass.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20technology%20had%20a%20brief%20ascendence%20used%20in%20professional%20settings%2C%20with%20businesses%20like%20Volkswagen%20and%20Boeing%20seeing%20increased%20productivity%20in%20workers%20wearing%20a%20headset%2C%20even%20the%20specialized%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftheres-a-new-version-of-google-glass-and-its-been-secretly-used-by-hundreds-of-factory-workers-for-the-last-two-years-2017-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BEnterprise%20Edition%26quot%3B%20of%20Google%20Glass%3C%2Fa%3E%20failed.%20There%20was%20simply%20not%20enough%20adoption.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228fdd44f2-14e0-42e8-a4ce-b1e454bfcfd5%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20you%20still%20buy%20Google%20Glass%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20find%20pairs%20of%20Google%20Glass%20for%20sale%20on%20Amazon%20and%20on%20eBay%20and%20at%20certain%20other%20platforms%2C%20so%20you%20can%20still%20purchase%20a%20set%20for%20yourself.%20But%20Google%20no%20longer%20offers%20any%20support%20for%20the%20device%2C%20thus%20if%20you%20have%20an%20issue%20with%20the%20hardware%2C%20you're%20on%20your%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20will%20be%20no%20further%20updates%2C%20no%20technical%20assistance%2C%20and%20certainly%20no%20repair%20or%20replacement%20of%20a%20Google%20Glass%20bought%20via%20a%20third-party%20seller.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20expect%20to%20pay%20between%20%24150%20and%20%2430