0speed%2C%20scientists%20are%20not%20alarmed%20this%20time.%20The%20safe%20distance%20between%20this%20asteroid%20and%20Earth%20is%20guaranteed%20by%20NASA%20to%20be%20around%202.75%20million%20miles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20majority%20of%20asteroids%20avoid%20Earth%2C%20a%20small%20number%20fall%20into%20a%20category%20known%20as%20potentially%20hazardous%20asteroids.%20These%20are%20large-more%20than%20460%20feet%20and%20their%20orbits%20carry%20them%20close%20to%20Earth's%20orbit%20around%20the%20Sun%2C%20at%204.6%20million%20miles%20(7.5%20million%20km).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20NASA's%20Asteroid%20Watch%20dashboard%20tracks%20asteroids%20and%20comets%20that%20will%20make%20relatively%20close%20approaches%20to%20Earth.%20The%20dashboard%20displays%20the%20date%20of%20closest%20approach%2C%20approximate%20object%20diameter%2C%20relative%20size%2C%20and%20distance%20from%20Earth%20for%20each%20encounter.%20It%20tracks%20asteroids%20that%20are%20within%207.5%20million%20kilometres%20of%20Earth%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20NASA%2C%20asteroids%20are%20left%20over%20from%20the%20formation%20of%20our%20solar%20system.%20Our%20solar%20system%20began%20about%204.6%20billion%20years%20ago%20when%20a%20big%20cloud%20of%20gas%20and%20dust%20collapsed.%20When%20this%20happened%2C%20most%20of%20the%20material%20fell%20to%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20cloud%20and%20formed%20the%20sun.%20Some%20of%20the%20condensing%20dust%20in%20the%20cloud%20became%20planets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20all%20asteroids%20are%20the%20same%20size%20and%20shape.%20Because%20asteroids%20are%20formed%20in%20different%20locations%20at%20different%20distances%20from%20the%20sun%2C%20no%20two%20asteroids%20are%20alike.%20Asteroids%20aren't%20all%20around%20like%20planets%20and%20have%20jagged%20and%20irregular%20shapes.%20Most%20asteroids%20are%20made%20of%20different%20kinds%20of%20rocks%2C%20but%20some%20have%20clays%20or%20metals%2C%20such%20as%20nickel%20and%20iron.%3C%2F