5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EVogue%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20her%20decision%20in%20an%20interview%20published%20on%20Sunday.%20She%20shared%20that%20she%20underwent%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffroze-my-eggs-cost-risks-worth-it-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eegg%20freezing%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20ages%2033%2C%2039%2C%20and%2042.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20interesting%20because%20my%2033-year-old%20eggs%20were%20great.%20My%2039-year-old%20eggs%3F%20None%20of%20them%20worked.%20As%20you%20get%20older%2C%20one%20month%20can%20have%20great%20eggs%2C%20the%20other%20not%20so%20much.%20Clearly%2C%20the%20month%20we%20did%20at%2039%20was%20not%20a%20good%20month%2C%26quot%3B%20Munn%20told%20Vogue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20chemotherapy%20and%20radiation%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mayoclinichealthsystem.org%2Fhometown-health%2Fspeaking-of-health%2Fcancer-treatment-and-fertility%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecan%20affect%20a%20person's%20fertility%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Munn%20said%20she%20and%20her%20husband%2C%20John%20Mulaney%2C%20decided%20to%20try%20freezing%20her%20eggs%20again%20before%20she%20started%20on%20any%20cancer%20treatment.%20The%20couple%20had%20welcomed%20their%20son%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpeople.com%2Fparents%2Fall-about-olivia-munn-and-john-mulaney-son%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMalcolm%20Hi%E1%BB%87p%20Mulaney%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20November%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJohn%20and%20I%20talked%20about%20it%20a%20lot%20and%20we%20don't%20feel%20like%20we're%20done%20growing%20our%20family%2C%20but%20didn't%20know%20if%20I%20would%20have%20to%20do%20chemotherapy%20or%20radiation%2C%26quot%3B%20Munn%20said.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20my%20diagnosis%2C%20we%20decided%20to%20try%20one%20more%20round%20of%20egg%20retrievals%20and%20hoped%20it%20was%20a%20good%20month.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMunn%20said%20they%20hoped%20to%20make%20just%20one%20embryo%20from%20this%20retrieval%20attempt.%20Thankfully%2C%20they%20were%20successful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20few%20hours%20later%2C%20we%20got%20the%20call%20from%20my%20doctor%2C%26quot%3B%20Munn%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20shared%20that%20we%20had%20two%20healthy%20embryos.%20John%20and%20I%20just%20started%20crying.%20It%20was%20just%20so%20exciting%20because%20not%20only%20did%20we%20get%20it%20in%20one%20retrieval%2C%20but%20it%20also%20meant%20that%20I%20didn't%20have%20to%20keep%20putting%20myself%20at%20risk.%20It%20was%20just%20amazing.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20her%20embryos%2C%20Munn%20says%20that%20she%20will%20likely%20go%20down%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwife-surrogate-pregnancy-made-better-dad-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurrogacy%3C%2Fa%3E%20route%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20have%20the%20ability%20to%20carry%20a%20baby%20anymore%2C%20so%20if%20we%20want%20to%20build%20our%20family%2C%20this%20is%20our%20option%2C%26quot%3B%20Munn%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20she%20used%20to%20be%20intimidated%20by%20that%20prospect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you're%20pregnant%20with%20your%20own%20baby%2C%20it's%20like%20teamwork%20%E2%80%94%20you%20and%20the%20baby%20working%20together%20to%20make%20their%20little%20life%20come%20true%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20doing%20all%20this%20work%20to%20eat%20well%2C%20try%20to%20not%20have%20anxiety%2C%20just%20do%20all%20the%20right%20things%20during%20the%20pregnancy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20not%20easy%20to%20find%20the%20right%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-to-be-a-professional-surrogate-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurrogate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20a%20surrogate%2C%20you%20have%20to%20try%20to%20go%20find%20a%20version%20of%20yourself%20somewhere%20out%20in%20the%20world.%20Somebody%20that%20you%20trust%20as%20much%20as%20yourself%20to%20live%20their%20life%20as%20a%20pregnant%20woman%20the%20same%20way%20that%20you%20would%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20representative%20for%20Munn%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20regular%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20with%20uteruses%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Freproductive-health%2Fhow-many-eggs-does-a-woman-have%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eborn%20with%20about%20one%20to%20two%20million%20eggs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20this%20number%20gradually%20decreases%20with%20age.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpowertodecide.org%2Fabout-us%2Fleadership%2Fraegan-mcdonald-mosley-md-mph%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERaegan%20McDonald-Mosley%2C%20MD%2C%20MPH%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20obstetrician-gynecologist%20and%20chief%20executive%20of%20Power%20to%20Decide%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20likelihood%20of%20getting%20pregnant%20generally%20peaks%20between%20the%20late%20teens%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.acog.org%2Fwomens-health%2Ffaqs%2Fhaving-a-baby-after-age-35-how-aging-affects-fertility-and-pregnancy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20and%20the%20late%2020s%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20egg%20freezing%20is%20mainly%20recommended%20for%20those%20who%20have%20to%20undergo%20cancer%20treatment%20that%20will%20affect%20their%20future%20fertility%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.acog.org%2Fwomens-health%2Ffaqs%2Fhaving-a-baby-after-age-35-how-aging-affects-fertility-and-pregnancy%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmerican%20College%20of%20Obstetricians%20and%20Gynecologists%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20the%20rise%20in%20hormone%20levels%2C%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hopkins